<h2 id="Syntax">Syntax</h2>

<pre class="twopartsyntaxbox"><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax" title="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax">Formal syntax</a>: <code><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/CSS_values_syntax#syntax-bg-image" title="none | &lt;image&gt;">&lt;bg-image&gt;</a><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Hash_mark_(.23)" title="Hash mark multiplier: The previous entity may appear 0, 1 or several times, each occurrence being separated from the previous one by a comma.">#</a></code>
</pre>

<pre>background-image: none
background-image: url(http://www.example.com/images/bck.png)

background-image: inherit
</pre>

<h3 id="Values">Values</h3>

<dl><dt><code>none</code></dt>
 <dd>Is a keyword denoting the absence of images.</dd>
 <dt><code>&lt;image&gt;</code></dt>
 <dd>Is an <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/image" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;image&gt;</code></a> denoting the image to display. There can be several of them, separated by commas, as <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Multiple_backgrounds" title="Multiple backgrounds">multiple backgrounds</a> are supported.</dd>
</dl>